casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Horton, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Horton, 105 Ohio St.3d 1209, 2005-Ohio-788.]

(No. 2004-0523 Submitted February 16, 2005 Decided March 16, 2005.)

{¶ 1} The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently accepted.

Moyer, C.J., Resnick, Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Connor, O’Donnell and Lanzinger, JJ., concur. *1210John D. Ferrero Jr., Stark County Prosecuting Attorney, and Kathleen 0. Tatarsky, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. David H. Bodiker, State Public Defender, and Stephen P. Hardwick, Assistant Public Defender, for appellant.
